        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deposit Security Act&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill increases the amount of deposit insurance available to noninterest-bearing transaction accounts through the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC) and the National Credit Union Administration (NCUA). Under current law, deposits are generally insured up to $250,000.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Specifically, noninterest-bearing transaction accounts at FDIC-insured depository institutions and at NCUA-insured credit unions must be insured up to $10 million. However, an institution or credit union may opt-out of this insurance during the 30-day period beginning on the date the program starts.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In addition, the maximum deposit insurance amount must be adjusted for inflation every two years.&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;!--tinycomments|2.1|data:application/json;base64,--&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
